SIMPLE: search
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Search
<hw>Search</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Searched</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Searching</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>serchen</ets>, <ets>cerchen</ets>, OF. <ets>cerchier</ets>, F.
<ets>chercher</ets>, L. <ets>circare</ets> to go about, fr. L.
<ets>circum</ets>, <ets>circa</ets>, around. See <er>Circle</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To look over or through, for the purpose of finding
something; to examine; to explore; <as>as, to <ex>search</ex> the
city</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Search</xex> the Scriptures.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>John v. 39.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They are come to <qex>search</qex> the house.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Search</qex> me, O God, and know my heart.</q> <rj><qau>Ps.
cxxxix. 23.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To inquire after; to look for; to seek.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will both <qex>search</qex> my sheep, and seek them out.</q>
<rj><qau>Ezek. xxxiv. 11.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Enough is left besides to <qex>search</qex> and know.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To examine or explore by feeling with an instrument;
to probe; <as>as, to <ex>search</ex> a wound</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To examine; to try; to put to the test.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To search out</b></col>, <cd>to seek till found; to find
by seeking; <as>as, to <ex>search out</ex> truth</as>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To explore; examine; scrutinize; seek;
investigate; pry into; inquire.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Search</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Search
<hw>Search</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To seek; to look for something;
to make inquiry, exploration, or examination; to hunt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Once more <qex>search</qex> with me.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It sufficeth that they have once with care sifted the matter, and
<qex>searched</qex> into all the particulars.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Search</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Search
<hw>Search</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF. <ets>cerche</ets>. See
<er>Search</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>The act of seeking or
looking for something; quest; inquiry; pursuit for finding something;
examination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thus the orb he roamed⟦br⟧
With narrow <qex>search</qex>, and with inspection deep⟦br⟧
Considered every creature.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor did my <qex>search</qex> of liberty begin⟦br⟧
Till my black hairs were changed upon my chin.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Right of search</b></col> <fld>(Mar. Law)</fld>, <cd>the
right of the lawfully commissioned cruisers of belligerent nations to
examine and search private merchant vessels on the high seas, for the
enemy's property or for articles contraband of war.</cd> --
<col><b>Search warrant</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>a warrant legally
issued, authorizing an examination or search of a house, or other place,
for goods stolen, secreted, or concealed.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Scrutiny; examination; exploration;
investigation; research; inquiry; quest; pursuit.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Searchable</ent>⟦br⟧
